column4: Qipco British Champions Long Distance Cup (Group 1)
column19: If TRAWLERMAN runs to the sort of level of his last three starts, he will surely win again. Sweet William may outstay Stay True.
column20: 4/9 Trawlerman, 5/1 Sweet William,  Stay True, 12/1 Al Qareem, 66/1 Saratoga
column36: Tough front-runner but Trawlerman gave him 3lb and a comprehensive beating at York
column37: Front-running 6yo who keeps pulling out more, with 12 wins now to his credit, including three of his four starts at Ascot; latest was over 1m4f two weeks ago, with three 1m6f wins earlier this season; he's never been at his best over this far, admittedly with stiff tasks but it's hard to ignore that Trawlerman gave him 3lb and a comprehensive beating at York in August.

column4: Qipco British Champions Long Distance Cup (Group 1)
column19: If TRAWLERMAN runs to the sort of level of his last three starts, he will surely win again. Sweet William may outstay Stay True.
column20: 4/9 Trawlerman, 5/1 Sweet William,  Stay True, 12/1 Al Qareem, 66/1 Saratoga
column36: Reliable but he found Trawlerman too tough to crack in their two clashes this season
column37: Headgear and Rab Havlin all starts; not straightforward but he nearly always gives his running and was third and second in the last two runnings of this race; he did not have the top stayers to worry about last month when winning his second Doncaster Cup and while he had the edge over third-placed Trawlerman in this 12 months ago, he's found that rival too tough to crack in their two clashes this season.

column4: Qipco British Champions Long Distance Cup (Group 1)
column19: If TRAWLERMAN runs to the sort of level of his last three starts, he will surely win again. Sweet William may outstay Stay True.
column20: 4/9 Trawlerman, 5/1 Sweet William,  Stay True, 12/1 Al Qareem, 66/1 Saratoga
column36: The outstanding stayer of this season; Gold Cup winner here; very much the one to beat
column37: Battling 7yo who can front-run (doesn't have to) and did so to pulverising effect in the Gold Cup here (2m4f) this June, winning by 7l; that's his career-best form but several runs are not far behind it, including his two other wins this season; latest was from Sweet William at York (2m); won this race in 2023, fair third last year and very much the one to beat this time.

column4: Qipco British Champions Long Distance Cup (Group 1)

column27: Lynch Bages Ltd & Camas Park Stud
column32: Derrick Smith & Mrs John Magnier & Michael Tabor
column36: Improved from the front in 1m6f/2m handicaps; pedigree is vastly more appealing than form
column37: Placed in his three maidens; improved for handicap win at Listowel (upped to 1m6f on heavy) and fifth of 20 in a useful handicap at Naas (2m, yielding) six days ago; both were from the front and maybe he'll try to make the running again, but pedigree (half-brother to high-class Capri and Tower Of London) is vastly more appealing than form for this stablemate of Stay True.

column36: St Leger 3rd; very classy prospect but he's not been shaping as if 2m is what he needs
column37: Won a 1m2f Leopardstown maiden and short-headed in 11.6f Lingfield Derby Trial before a three-month absence; returned with further improved efforts when close up in the Great Voltigeur at York (1m4f, good to firm) and the St Leger at Doncaster (14.5f, soft) and he threatened to win in both those races; he therefore remains a very classy prospect but he's not been shaping as if this extra distance is what he needs.

column4: Qipco British Champions Sprint Stakes (Group 1)

column4: Qipco British Champions Sprint Stakes (Group 1)

column4: Qipco British Champions Sprint Stakes (Group 1)

column4: Qipco British Champions Fillies & Mares Stakes (Group 1)

column4: Qipco British Champions Fillies & Mares Stakes (Group 1)
column20: 11/4 Kalpana, 4/1 Estrange, 6/1 Waardah, 7/1 Quisisana,  Bedtime Story, 9/1 Wemightakedlongway, 12/1 Danielle,  One Look, 14/1 Latakia, 20/1 Ballet Slippers

column4: Qipco British Champions Fillies & Mares Stakes (Group 1)

column4: Qipco British Champions Fillies & Mares Stakes (Group 1)

column36: Lightly raced 3yo who, if ground is okay, can find further improvement to have a big shout

column4: Qipco British Champions Fillies & Mares Stakes (Group 1)

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)

column37: Out of an unraced sister to smart jumper Great Endeavour; kept on well for third on Irish point debut in April (yielding ground) and was bought for 75,000euros soon afterwards; no surprise if he features on rules debut.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 5/2 Hot To Go, 4/1 Calvino, 9/2 Havefunontherun,  Le Soleil Reve, 8/1 Madajovy, 10/1 Grey Lagoon, 12/1 Jackomy, 20/1 Kapitein Kool, 50/1 Idaho Bridge, 66/1 Fight My Fire, 100/1 El Arco
column36: Showed only minor promise in three bumpers last season; hurdling debut today
column37: Showed only minor promise in three bumpers last season and needs to take a big step forward on this hurdling debut.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 5/2 Hot To Go, 4/1 Calvino, 9/2 Havefunontherun,  Le Soleil Reve, 8/1 Madajovy, 10/1 Grey Lagoon, 12/1 Jackomy, 20/1 Kapitein Kool, 50/1 Idaho Bridge, 66/1 Fight My Fire, 100/1 El Arco

column37: Half-brother to fairly useful hurdler Below The Radar; dam unraced sister to smart jumper Bennys King; looked set to make winning Irish point debut before last-fence fall in March (yielding ground) and subsequently change hands for £50,000; makes rules debut here; market helpful.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)

column37: Made the frame in two bumpers in the spring (good to soft/good) and had excuse (irregular heartbeat) when pulled-up odds-on favourite over hurdles in June; this race looks much more competitive but he has possibilities if all is well.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 5/2 Hot To Go, 4/1 Calvino, 9/2 Havefunontherun,  Le Soleil Reve, 8/1 Madajovy, 10/1 Grey Lagoon, 12/1 Jackomy, 20/1 Kapitein Kool, 50/1 Idaho Bridge, 66/1 Fight My Fire, 100/1 El Arco
column36: Tailed off (raced too freely) when 33-1 for Chepstow bumper in March; hurdle debut
column37: Tailed off (raced too freely) when 33-1 for Chepstow bumper in March; hooded for this hurdling debut.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 5/2 Hot To Go, 4/1 Calvino, 9/2 Havefunontherun,  Le Soleil Reve, 8/1 Madajovy, 10/1 Grey Lagoon, 12/1 Jackomy, 20/1 Kapitein Kool, 50/1 Idaho Bridge, 66/1 Fight My Fire, 100/1 El Arco
column36: Flat-bred 4yo who was soundly beaten after racing too freely in two bumpers last season
column37: Flat-bred 4yo who was soundly beaten after racing too freely in two bumpers last season; can only be watched on this hurdling debut.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 5/2 Hot To Go, 4/1 Calvino, 9/2 Havefunontherun,  Le Soleil Reve, 8/1 Madajovy, 10/1 Grey Lagoon, 12/1 Jackomy, 20/1 Kapitein Kool, 50/1 Idaho Bridge, 66/1 Fight My Fire, 100/1 El Arco
column36: Bought for £165,000 after promising Irish point debut in February; must be considered
column37: Half-brother to useful Irish hurdler Custom Taylor; made most of the running when close second in six-runner Irish point in February (heavy ground), form that was recently well adverted by the winner in a Chepstow bumper; joined Twiston-Davies stable for £165,000 in March; must be considered on rules debut.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 5/2 Hot To Go, 4/1 Calvino, 9/2 Havefunontherun,  Le Soleil Reve, 8/1 Madajovy, 10/1 Grey Lagoon, 12/1 Jackomy, 20/1 Kapitein Kool, 50/1 Idaho Bridge, 66/1 Fight My Fire, 100/1 El Arco
column36: Displayed promise in three bumpers but might be one for further down the line
column37: Displayed promise in three bumpers, perhaps most notably when staying-on fifth of 13 at Kempton (good) on second occasion; makes hurdling debut after 161-day break, though, and might be one for further down the line.

column4: British Stallion Studs EBF 'National Hunt' Novices' Hurdle (Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 5/2 Hot To Go, 4/1 Calvino, 9/2 Havefunontherun,  Le Soleil Reve, 8/1 Madajovy, 10/1 Grey Lagoon, 12/1 Jackomy, 20/1 Kapitein Kool, 50/1 Idaho Bridge, 66/1 Fight My Fire, 100/1 El Arco
column27: Sca La Perigne, Ecurie Du Chene, Roger-Y
column36: Absent since winning junior hurdle win in February but runs without a penalty here
column37: Built upon encouraging debut when winning five-runner junior hurdle at Hereford (2m, soft) in February; not seen again since but runs without a penalty here and ought to make his presence felt.

column36: Inconsistent last season but won when fresh a year ago and resumes on good mark
column37: Inconsistent last season and absent since tame effort in March but won when fresh a year ago, at Chepstow (2m7f, good to soft), and begins his new campaign from a good mark.

column4: Weatherbys & Birdie Calendars Conditional Jockeys' Handicap Chase
column20: 15/8 Of Corse I Can, 7/2 Testflight, 9/2 Lock Out, 6/1 Esperti, 7/1 Moonlight Artist, 9/1 Blackacre

column20: 15/8 Of Corse I Can, 7/2 Testflight, 9/2 Lock Out, 6/1 Esperti, 7/1 Moonlight Artist, 9/1 Blackacre

column20: 15/8 Of Corse I Can, 7/2 Testflight, 9/2 Lock Out, 6/1 Esperti, 7/1 Moonlight Artist, 9/1 Blackacre
column36: Game C&D winner this summer and now back on same mark; likely contender
column37: Rallied well to win small-field C&D (good) chase off today's mark in July and reverts to fences after perfectly respectable hurdle run from out of the weights here last month; likely contender.

column4: Weatherbys & Birdie Calendars Conditional Jockeys' Handicap Chase
column20: 15/8 Of Corse I Can, 7/2 Testflight, 9/2 Lock Out, 6/1 Esperti, 7/1 Moonlight Artist, 9/1 Blackacre
column32: The Cheltenham & South West Racing Club
column36: Battled well for Warwick win in April; two heavy defeats followed; back from a break
column37: Battled on gamely for narrow win at Warwick (3m, good) in April but suffered heavy defeats on next two outings (latter was over C&D) and needs to have been refreshed by 136-day break.

column4: Weatherbys & Birdie Calendars Conditional Jockeys' Handicap Chase
column20: 15/8 Of Corse I Can, 7/2 Testflight, 9/2 Lock Out, 6/1 Esperti, 7/1 Moonlight Artist, 9/1 Blackacre
column27: G F A Du Pont Rouge
column36: Came good at Fontwell (3m2f) this month and remains unexposed over this sort of trip
column37: 0-12 over hurdles but came good over fences at second attempt, in five-runner contest at Fontwell (3m2f, good) a fortnight ago; only 2lb higher here and still very unexposed over this sort of trip; good chance.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column36: Safely held on recent stable debut but that came after a long layoff; may fare better here
column37: Useful and versatile when trained in Ireland by Willie Mullins; returned from long absence with down-the-field finish for new stable at Market Rasen (2m, good) three weeks ago but some positives can be drawn from that run and he might come on for the outing.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column27: Natton House Thoroughbreds & Mr G Bishop
column36: Well held at Aintree festival but earlier Newbury win makes him of interest here
column37: Never really got competitive at Aintree festival in April but his front-running win at Newbury (2m, good to soft) two starts ago makes him of interest here and, after only nine hurdle runs, he's not yet fully exposed.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column36: Held on gamely to make all in small field at Southwell this month; now 5-17 over hurdles
column37: Held on gamely to make all in four-runner race at Southwell (2m, good) this month and is now 5-17 over hurdles; nudged up 2lb to new career-high mark but still enters calculations.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column36: Battled well over C&D in June and has now won five of his last six; back from a break
column37: Very progressive 7yo who battled well for narrow C&D (good) success in June and has now won five of his last six races; has fitness to prove after 136-day break but may still have more to offer.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column36: Low-mileage 5yo; creditable fifth in major Haydock handicap on latest outing in May
column37: Dual winner in novice company last season and signed off in April with very respectable fifth of 16 in Swinton Handicap at Haydock (1m7f, good); major player in these calmer waters if fully tuned up after break.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column36: Maiden hurdle winner; well held in both handicap hurdles; off since poor Flat run in June
column37: Won Taunton maiden (2m, good to soft) in February but was safely held in both subsequent handicap hurdes and has been absent since running as though something was amiss on the Flat in June.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column36: Useful Flat racer; 2-3 over hurdles in the spring; faces tougher task on handicap debut
column37: Useful Flat racer who was 2-3 in novice/maiden hurdles for Paul Nicholls in the spring; tackles much stronger opposition on this handicap hurdle debut and his tendency to race too freely is a nagging concern but, nevertheless, he's still very unexposed over jumps.

column4: Wollens Full Spectrum Law Handicap Hurdle
column20: 5/2 Dance And Glance, 7/2 Courageous Strike, 4/1 American Land, 11/2 Manuelito,  Bluegrass, 12/1 Tax For Max, 25/1 Cornish Storm, 33/1 St Lukes Chelsea
column36: Safely held on handicap hurdle debut in January and effectively 5lb higher here
column37: Close second in Fontwell juvenile hurdle (2m1f, soft) last December but absent since low-key handicap debut the following month and competes from 7lb out of the weights here.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: Dual C&D winner in May and placed in quite valuable contest last time; big player
column37: Won twice over C&D (good) in May and arguably posted another career-best performance when placed in quite valuable contest at Cartmel (2m6f, good) in July; big player if still in same form after three-month break.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: Ended last season in excellent form over 2m4f; may have needed recent 2m run
column37: Made excellent progress towards end of last season, winning three consecutive 2m4f handicaps (good/good to soft); not seen to quite the same effect when reappearing over 2m last month but may kick on again now he's back up in trip and with that run behind him.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: Returned from latest spell in Jersey with good second at Ludlow this month; respected
column37: Won for Harry Derham at Wincanton (2m5f, good) a year ago and returned from latest spell in Jersey with close second under regular rider Victoria Malzard at Ludlow (2m5f, good to firm) this month; respected.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column32: S Clare G Kennington & C Knowles
column36: Went close over C&D last month but this race looks more competitive; others preferred
column37: Returned from four-month break with close second of five over C&D last month and competes off the same mark today but is not one to rely upon too heavily and today's race looks more competitive.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: Back in good nick over C&D last month but may find others better handicapped today
column37: Won three times in early part of year and was back in good nick when close fourth (hampered close home) over C&D (good) last month but may find others better handicapped in this stronger race; cheekpieces refitted.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: Pulled up on latest rules start in May 2024 but has won seven points since; interesting
column37: Not seen under rules since pulled up in 3m Wexford handicap hurdle in May 2024 but won seven consecutive points from December to May and it will be interesting to see how he fares here.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: 3-3 in blinkers towards end of last season; returns from six-month break here
column37: 3-3 since swapping cheekpieces for blinkers, the latest win gained at Haydock (3m, good) in April; subsequent six-month break may have checked her momentum but today's drop back in trip should not be a problem.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: Returned from break with two below-par runs last month; headgear missing again today
column37: Won twice off much reduced marks when upped to 3m and fitted with cheekpieces last December but returned from break with two below-par runs here last month (3m2f/2m5f) and the headgear is missing again today.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column36: Made all on heavy ground in February but not seen again since; no headgear today
column37: Bounced back to form with front-running win at Ffos Las (2m4f, heavy; second run in cheekpieces) in February; still well handicapped on older form but we haven't seen him again since and today's drier ground is probably not ideal; no headgear this time.

column4: Remembering Len & Pam Cartwright Handicap Hurdle
column20: 4/1 Al Sayah, 5/1 Busy Being Busy,  Diplomatie,  Elusiveness, 8/1 El Capitaine, 10/1 Striking A Pose,  Coconut Twist,  Stinginhisstep, 16/1 Despereaux,  Moorland Rambler
column32: A Leach And D V Gardner
column36: Close third of five over C&D last month but has more on his plate in deeper race today
column37: Dual 2m2f course winner this season; rebounded from two lesser efforts when close third of five (just behind Striking A Pose) over C&D (good) last month but has more on his plate in this deeper race.

column4: Paul Ferguson's Jumpers To Follow Intermediate Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 4/11 Blueking d'Oroux, 5/1 Riskintheground, 6/1 Lookaway, 25/1 Theformismighty, 50/1 Gyenyame
column36: In career-best form when winning twice in spring; also ran well in Summer Plate; respected
column37: In career-best form in April, winning at Ayr (2m4f, good to soft) and Cheltenham (2m4f, good; Grade 2 handicap), and gave another good account when fourth in Summer Plate at Market Rasen (2m5f, good) in July; faces a tough opponent here but ought to make his presence felt again.

column4: Paul Ferguson's Jumpers To Follow Intermediate Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 4/11 Blueking d'Oroux, 5/1 Riskintheground, 6/1 Lookaway, 25/1 Theformismighty, 50/1 Gyenyame
column36: Runner-up in two Class 4 Taunton handicaps in February/March; up against it here
column37: Seemingly aided by blinkers when runner-up in two Class 4 handicap chases at Taunton (2m5f/2m7f) in February/March but can't be recommended in this company.

column4: Paul Ferguson's Jumpers To Follow Intermediate Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 4/11 Blueking d'Oroux, 5/1 Riskintheground, 6/1 Lookaway, 25/1 Theformismighty, 50/1 Gyenyame
column36: Absent since last November but reverts to hurdling on a good mark; 3-3 at Uttoxeter
column37: Front-runner who was chasing during very light campaign last season and has been absent since November; back hurdling on a good mark and has 3-3 strike-rate at Uttoxeter; had wind op in March; contender if fully tuned up.

column4: Paul Ferguson's Jumpers To Follow Intermediate Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 4/11 Blueking d'Oroux, 5/1 Riskintheground, 6/1 Lookaway, 25/1 Theformismighty, 50/1 Gyenyame
column36: Developed into a useful handicap chaser last season but faces a tough assignment here
column37: Developed into a useful handicap chaser once cheekpieces were added last season and could plausibly have more improvement to come this term; however, he was pulled up on latest outing in May and faces a tough assignment here.

column4: Paul Ferguson's Jumpers To Follow Intermediate Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 4/11 Blueking d'Oroux, 5/1 Riskintheground, 6/1 Lookaway, 25/1 Theformismighty, 50/1 Gyenyame
column36: Smart staying hurdler who has very good chance at the weights on this chasing debut
column37: Smart staying hurdling who looked as good as ever when ending last season with Grade 2 win from the front at Sandown (2m5f, good); will be very hard to beat on these terms if he jumps adequately on his chasing debut.

column4: Torbay Weekly Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Siam Park, 11/4 Jaitroplaclasse, 5/1 Nordic Tiger,  Haas Boy, 9/1 Authoceltic
column27: L De Premont, G De Premont & T Van De
column36: Out of form over hurdles last season but makes chasing debut from dangerous mark
column37: Three-time hurdle winner in early 2024; out of form last season and makes chasing debut with quite a bit to prove but will be very dangerous in this grade if revitalised by seven-month break.

column4: Torbay Weekly Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Siam Park, 11/4 Jaitroplaclasse, 5/1 Nordic Tiger,  Haas Boy, 9/1 Authoceltic
column36: Won first three chases and lost out only narrowly when attempting four-timer; good chance
column37: Launched chasing career with three consecutive wins (2m-2m3f) in February/March and lost out only by a short head when attempting four-timer at Plumpton (2m3f, good) in April; has fitness to prove after six-month absence but still commands respect.

column4: Torbay Weekly Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Siam Park, 11/4 Jaitroplaclasse, 5/1 Nordic Tiger,  Haas Boy, 9/1 Authoceltic
column27: E A R L Haras Du Mondant Et Al
column36: 0-7 over hurdles; may have needed recent run; improvement required on chase debut
column37: Returned from one-year absence with low-key run in 2m4f maiden hurdle last month (raced too freely) and is now 0-7 in that sphere; entitled to have benefited from that outing but needs this switch to chasing to enable improvement.

column4: Torbay Weekly Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Siam Park, 11/4 Jaitroplaclasse, 5/1 Nordic Tiger,  Haas Boy, 9/1 Authoceltic
column27: David Lumet & Dr V Catherine Lumet
column36: Made all in small-field C&D contest last month; recent 4lb rise not excessive
column37: Made all to beat three rivals over C&D (good to soft) last month, opening his chasing account at the seventh attempt; recent 4lb rise does look excessive and further progress is certainly not out of the question.

column4: Torbay Weekly Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Siam Park, 11/4 Jaitroplaclasse, 5/1 Nordic Tiger,  Haas Boy, 9/1 Authoceltic
column27: S C E A Ecurie Jc Laisis
column36: Not at best for Emma Lavelle last season; now with another new stable; market may guide
column37: Very well handicapped on old hurdling form for Charlie Longsdon but didn't really fire during four-race campaign for Emma Lavelle last season and still has quite a bit to prove over fences; changed hands for 3,200euros in April; sports first-time cheekpieces here; first runner under rules for Chester Williams; market may guide.

column4: Jodie Standing's Point-To-Point Recruits Open National Hunt Flat Race (Category 1 Elimination) (GBB)
column20: 7/4 Soldier Reeves, 5/2 Great Dance, 100/30 Not Now, 11/2 Hobbson's Day, 14/1 Peaky Girl
column32: G Snell And Miss E Snell
column36: Half-brother to five French Flat winners; market helpful on debut
column37: 11,000gns foal; ninth foal; half-brother to five French Flat winners (one useful); dam French Flat winner, half-sister to a Listed winner; stable has very respectable bumper strike-rate (12%); market helpful.

column4: Jodie Standing's Point-To-Point Recruits Open National Hunt Flat Race (Category 1 Elimination) (GBB)
column20: 7/4 Soldier Reeves, 5/2 Great Dance, 100/30 Not Now, 11/2 Hobbson's Day, 14/1 Peaky Girl
column27: Scea Haras De Tonnecourt, E & H Petit
column36: 70,000euros 3yo; out of unraced sister to high-class jumper Nickname; one to consider
column37: 70,000euros 3yo; eighth foal; closely related to a French 2m2f hurdle winner, half-brother to two other French winners (Flat/hurdle); dam unraced sister to high-class jumper Nickname; with a good stable; no surprise if he poses a threat on debut.

column4: Jodie Standing's Point-To-Point Recruits Open National Hunt Flat Race (Category 1 Elimination) (GBB)
column20: 7/4 Soldier Reeves, 5/2 Great Dance, 100/30 Not Now, 11/2 Hobbson's Day, 14/1 Peaky Girl
column36: Bought for £95,000 after promising Irish point debut in March; must be considered
column37: Half-brother to fairly useful Irish hurdler Ms Agartha Yeats; dam useful 2m hurdler; close second of three in soft-ground Irish point in March, after which he joined top stable for £95,000; must be considered.

column4: Jodie Standing's Point-To-Point Recruits Open National Hunt Flat Race (Category 1 Elimination) (GBB)
column20: 7/4 Soldier Reeves, 5/2 Great Dance, 100/30 Not Now, 11/2 Hobbson's Day, 14/1 Peaky Girl

column4: Jodie Standing's Point-To-Point Recruits Open National Hunt Flat Race (Category 1 Elimination) (GBB)
column20: 7/4 Soldier Reeves, 5/2 Great Dance, 100/30 Not Now, 11/2 Hobbson's Day, 14/1 Peaky Girl
column36: Second foal from smart Irish hurdler Let's Dance; looks the part on paper
column37: 110,000euros 2yo; second foal; sister to a French 2m2f hurdle winner; dam smart 2m-2m4f hurdle winner, half-sister to useful jumper Sail Away and a bumper winner; looks the part on paper.

column4: Nigel Reeve 60th Birthday Celebration Female Jockeys' Handicap Hurdle (Female Jockeys & Amateurs')

column37: By a top sire and hails from a quality damline; not much market confidence on debut at Listowel but ran an encouraging race when looked green; was just behind Voladora Nora then but could overturn that form with the run under her girth; possibilities.

column37: Beaten 11l in bumpers at Ballinrobe and Listowel, finishing just in front of today's rival Tumbling In on latter occasion; might struggle to confirm the form with that rival and has others to worry about too.
